 Nefsky discover some surprising answers. The theologies and the historical and ethnic configurations of Protestant Canada, encompassing religious communities from the United Church to the Quakers, are brought into relief against the background of the Great Depression, the rise of fascism in Europe and the resurgence of nativism in Canadian society. The authors conclude their study with an evaluation of the limits to Protestant influence in Canada and the dilemmas faced by religious communities and persons of conscience when confronted by the realities of power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAntisemitismzCanada. 0aAntisémitismexCanada. 0aChristianisme et antisémitisme. 0aChristianity and antisemitismxHistoryx20th centuryxCanada. 0aChristianity and antisemitismxProtestant churchesxHistoryx20th century. 0aChristianity and antisemitismxProtestant churchesxHistoryy20th century. 0aChristianity and antisemitismzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aChristianity and antisemitism. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xForeign public opinion, Canadian. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945). 0aHolocauste, 1939-1945. 0aProtestant churcheszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aÉglises protestantesxHistoirex20e sièclexCanada. 4aHistory: Canadian History. 4aHistory: Jewish Studies. 4aReligion. 7aHISTORY / Canada / General.2bisacsh1 aNefsky, Marilyn F., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920840740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889208407423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889208407/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP